41__RCSID("$NetBSD: libelf_align.c,v 1.4 2016/02/20 02:43:42 christos Exp $");
42ELFTC_VCSID("Id: libelf_align.c 3174 2015-03-27 17:13:41Z emaste ");
43
44struct align {
45 unsigned int a32;
46 unsigned int a64;
47};
48
49#if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__lint__)
50#define MALIGN(N) { \
51 .a32 = __alignof__(Elf32_##N), \
52 .a64 = __alignof__(Elf64_##N) \
53 }
54#define MALIGN64(V) { \
55 .a32 = 0, \
56 .a64 = __alignof__(Elf64_##V) \
57 }
58#define MALIGN_WORD() { \
59 .a32 = __alignof__(int32_t), \
60 .a64 = __alignof__(int64_t) \
61 }
62#else
63#error Need the __alignof__ builtin.
64#endif
65#define UNSUPPORTED() { \
66 .a32 = 0, \
67 .a64 = 0 \
68 }
69
70static struct align malign[ELF_T_NUM] = {
71 [ELF_T_ADDR] = MALIGN(Addr),
72 [ELF_T_BYTE] = { .a32 = 1, .a64 = 1 },
73 [ELF_T_CAP] = MALIGN(Cap),
74 [ELF_T_DYN] = MALIGN(Dyn),
75 [ELF_T_EHDR] = MALIGN(Ehdr),
76 [ELF_T_HALF] = MALIGN(Half),
77 [ELF_T_LWORD] = MALIGN(Lword),
78 [ELF_T_MOVE] = MALIGN(Move),
79 [ELF_T_MOVEP] = UNSUPPORTED(),
80 [ELF_T_NOTE] = MALIGN(Nhdr),
81 [ELF_T_OFF] = MALIGN(Off),
82 [ELF_T_PHDR] = MALIGN(Phdr),
83 [ELF_T_REL] = MALIGN(Rel),
84 [ELF_T_RELA] = MALIGN(Rela),
85 [ELF_T_SHDR] = MALIGN(Shdr),
86 [ELF_T_SWORD] = MALIGN(Sword),
87 [ELF_T_SXWORD] = MALIGN64(Sxword),
88 [ELF_T_SYM] = MALIGN(Sym),
89 [ELF_T_SYMINFO] = MALIGN(Syminfo),
90 [ELF_T_VDEF] = MALIGN(Verdef),
91 [ELF_T_VNEED] = MALIGN(Verneed),
92 [ELF_T_WORD] = MALIGN(Word),
93 [ELF_T_XWORD] = MALIGN64(Xword),
94 [ELF_T_GNUHASH] = MALIGN_WORD()
95};
96
97unsigned int
98_libelf_malign(Elf_Type t, int elfclass)
99{
100 if (t >= ELF_T_NUM || (int) t < 0)
101 return (0);
102
103 return (elfclass == ELFCLASS32 ? malign[t].a32 :
104 malign[t].a64);
105}
106
107#define FALIGN(A32,A64) { .a32 = (A32), .a64 = (A64) }
108
109static struct align falign[ELF_T_NUM] = {
110 [ELF_T_ADDR] = FALIGN(4,8),
111 [ELF_T_BYTE] = FALIGN(1,1),
112 [ELF_T_CAP] = FALIGN(4,8),
113 [ELF_T_DYN] = FALIGN(4,8),
114 [ELF_T_EHDR] = FALIGN(4,8),
115 [ELF_T_HALF] = FALIGN(2,2),
116 [ELF_T_LWORD] = FALIGN(8,8),
117 [ELF_T_MOVE] = FALIGN(8,8),
118 [ELF_T_MOVEP] = UNSUPPORTED(),
119 [ELF_T_NOTE] = FALIGN(1,1),
120 [ELF_T_OFF] = FALIGN(4,8),
121 [ELF_T_PHDR] = FALIGN(4,8),
122 [ELF_T_REL] = FALIGN(4,8),
123 [ELF_T_RELA] = FALIGN(4,8),
124 [ELF_T_SHDR] = FALIGN(4,8),
125 [ELF_T_SWORD] = FALIGN(4,4),
126 [ELF_T_SXWORD] = FALIGN(0,8),
127 [ELF_T_SYM] = FALIGN(4,8),
128 [ELF_T_SYMINFO] = FALIGN(2,2),
129 [ELF_T_VDEF] = FALIGN(4,4),
130 [ELF_T_VNEED] = FALIGN(4,4),
131 [ELF_T_WORD] = FALIGN(4,4),
132 [ELF_T_XWORD] = FALIGN(0,8),
133 [ELF_T_GNUHASH] = FALIGN(4,8)
134};
135
136unsigned int
137_libelf_falign(Elf_Type t, int elfclass)
138{
139 if (t >= ELF_T_NUM || (int) t < 0)
140 return (0);
141
142 return (elfclass == ELFCLASS32 ? falign[t].a32 :
143 falign[t].a64);
144}
